    <h1 class="main-title">Data Privacy Challenges in the Digital Age</h1>

    <section class="challenges-section">
      <h2>What Are the Key Challenges for Individuals and Companies?</h2>
      <p class="intro-text">As reported by <em>(Bisht, 2024)</em>, here are some of the most significant data privacy challenges faced today:</p>

      <div class="table-container">
        <table class="challenges-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>#</th>
              <th>Challenge</th>
              <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>1</td><td>Lack of Data Transparency</td><td>Apps collect personal data without clearly informing users about how it’s used or shared.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2</td><td>Risks of Cloud Computing</td><td>Cloud storage increases exposure to breaches, especially with weak security or foreign storage laws.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>3</td><td>Weak Data Protection Laws</td><td>Inconsistent or weak laws allow unchecked data collection and misuse.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>4</td><td>Frequent Data Breaches</td><td>Human error, hacking, or theft often exposes sensitive personal data.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>5</td><td>Excessive Data Retention</td><td>Holding onto data too long increases risks of leaks or unethical use.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>6</td><td>Emerging Technologies (AI/IoT)</td><td>AI and IoT collect large data volumes, risking misuse or unauthorized profiling.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="enforcement-section">
      <h2>Challenges in Enforcing Data Privacy</h2>

      <div class="enforcement-content">
        <div class="text-block">
          <h3>Compliance and Implementation Difficulties</h3>
          <p>Despite strict regulations, compliance remains difficult—especially for small businesses—due to high costs and complexity <em>(Tankard, 2016)</em>. Multinational companies also face legal conflicts across jurisdictions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-block">
          <h3>Technical Limitations</h3>
          <p>Balancing data utility and privacy is challenging: heavy anonymization reduces research value <em>(Ohm, 2010)</em>, while de-anonymization attacks show even "secure" data can be re-identified <em>(Shmatikov, 2008)</em>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-block">
          <h3>Emerging Privacy Threats</h3>
          <p>AI and big data analytics can extract private details from seemingly anonymous datasets. IoT expands surveillance risks, increasing exposure to leaks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
